        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Just for the hell of it (way back before Velious even came out), I make a 1st level gnome and had a friend of mine transfer a pile of cash to him.  I then proceeded to try to make some Stalking Probes at level one.  Failed a lot, but I did get a rare sucess now and then.  So, even with just the basic tinkering skill, it can be done.</P><P>Now the bad part, even assuming you got a sucess every single time, your still plunking down 14 plat per Probe.  The beauty of the Elder Beads is that you can stay in Lich/Demi-Lich form indefinately, and just pop out an eye whenever you feel like casting Bond or Vexing.  If you use the Probes, your either going to a) be reluctant to use them because of the charges, which defeats the whole point of having them, or b) end up spending a lot of cash to make enough of these to satisfy your needs.  Either way, you would be better off just getting or even buying the beads.</P><P><IMG src="http://members.spree.com/funngames/qazjax/pharm/farmerpump.jpg"></P><P>"Having been left with little other choice by Verant, Elmer the retired old Necromancer, had little left to do but either farm or pump."</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

